      <Conclusion>Conclusions: Smoking cessation treatment resulted in significant reductions in daily smoking and modest smoking abstinence rates without having an adverse impact on substance abuse rehabilitation when given concurrently with outpatient substance abuse treatment. Substance abuse treatment programs should not hesitate to implement SC for established patients. (Article (Peer-reviewed), PDF, English, 2007)</Conclusion>
